    <data key="d0">Australian Dolphins: Machine Learning for Swim standing Predictions</data>
    <data key="d1">https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1VcpCVe3tLQ</data>
    <data key="d2">The Australian Dolphins swimming team uses machine learning on AWS to predict swim times, standings, and optimal relay lineups. Swimmer data is curated via Glue into S3, queried via Athena, and used by SageMaker for training. A verification Lambda checks predictions before they are exposed via API Gateway to coaches. Step Functions orchestrates the retraining pipeline.</data>
    <data key="d3">compute_intensive, interactive</data>
    <data key="d4">True</data>
  </graph>
</graphml>
